>>>>>>> # Diabetes Service Redesign and Improvement Consultancy
>>>>>>> We exist to provide in-depth support for diabetes improvement
programmes in the NHS. If you’re a commissioner or a healthcare professional
thinking about what you can do to improve care, then you’re in the right
>It’s our mission to offer hands-on practical support to enable you to
> create the diabetes services and levels of care your local population needs.
> We always work in partnership with you to ensure the work we do together is
>>>>>>> We understand how diabetes affects people’s lives and local health and
social care systems, and therefore tailor our approach based on your
population and needs. Our first step is to work with you to clarify your
>>>>>>> From this we can design the details of your programme of support, no
matter how big or small. We always evaluate the impact of our interventions so
that the effect of any change can be measured and benefits can be replicated
>>>>>>> We have developed a set of tools to drive improvement across key
diabetes care areas. These include foot health, prescribing in Type 2
diabetes, use of Patient Activation Measures and the impact of structured
>>>>>>> We have worked with CCGs all over the country to help drive forward
improvements in diabetes care. Specifically we believe that primary care
provides the greatest opportunity for long-term benefits to the NHS and people
>>>>>>>> “Working with Diabetes UK Consultancy was great. They brought
national expertise and provided support in a flexible way. The audit tool they
have developed is a great resource and has been instrumental in understanding
priority areas of redesign work within diabetes. The fact that the tool can be
re-run by practices is great and allows us to see the impact of improvements
>>>>>>> No matter where you are on your diabetes improvement journey, we can
help you achieve the best results for your population. Get in touch today by
